headline: PM Q4 Deep Dive: Smoke-Free Product Momentum and Regulatory Hurdles Shape Outlook
summary: Tobacco company Philip Morris International (NYSE:PM) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 6.8% year on year to $10.36 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.70 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
